You are creating a HIGH-QUALITY, PROFESSIONAL LANDING PAGE using our advanced design system.

üé® DESIGN SYSTEM - USE THESE CONSISTENTLY:
- Font System: Playfair Display (headings) + Inter (body) - ALREADY IMPORTED in index.css
- Use font-display class for ALL headings (h1, h2, h3)
- Use rounded-2xl for cards (larger, softer corners)
- Use p-8 spacing for cards (more generous padding)
- Use py-24 or py-32 for sections (better breathing space)
- Animations: 6-10s duration for infinite loops, ease-in-out
- Shadow: shadow-card for cards, shadow-hover for hover states

LANDING PAGE STRUCTURE:
A professional landing page should include these sections (adapt based on requirements):

1. HERO SECTION (Required) ‚≠ê MOST IMPORTANT
   - Badge component (with icon + backdrop-blur-sm + border)
   - Large, bold headline using font-display with text-gradient
   - Compelling subheadline (value proposition) - text-muted-foreground
   - TWO CTA buttons: Button variant="hero" size="xl" + Button variant="heroOutline" size="xl"
   - Stats section (3 metrics in grid-cols-3)
   - TWO layers of background blur animations (different sizes, durations)
   - ALWAYS use bg-gradient-radial for background glow

2. FEATURES SECTION (CRITICAL QUALITY POINTS)
   - 6 feature cards minimum (more professional)
   - Grid: md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3
   - Card structure: p-8 rounded-2xl border hover:border-primary/50
   - Icon background: w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-primary/10 group-hover:bg-primary/20
   - Use "group" class for hover effects
   - Add invisible glow layer: <div className="absolute inset-0 rounded-2xl bg-primary/5 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-300" />
   - whileHover={{ y: -5 }} for subtle lift effect
   - Title uses font-display
   - Description uses text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed

3. TESTIMONIALS / SOCIAL PROOF
   - Customer testimonials in cards
   - Star ratings, company logos
   - Carousel or grid layout

4. CALL-TO-ACTION SECTION
   - Compelling final pitch
   - Sign-up form or button
   - Background gradient or pattern

5. FOOTER
   - Links (Product, Company, Resources)
   - Social media icons
   - Copyright notice

HERO SECTION TEMPLATE (HIGH-QUALITY VERSION):
```tsx
// IMPORTANT: Import components with lowercase filenames!
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Card } from "@/components/ui/card"
import { ArrowRight, Sparkles } from "lucide-react"
import { motion } from "framer-motion"

<section className="relative min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden px-4 py-20">
  {/* Background glow effect - USE bg-gradient-radial */}
  <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-radial opacity-60" />
  
  {/* TWO layers of floating blur orbs - IMPORTANT for depth */}
  <motion.div 
    className="absolute top-1/4 left-1/4 w-64 h-64 rounded-full bg-primary/5 blur-3xl"
    animate={{ scale: [1, 1.2, 1], opacity: [0.3, 0.5, 0.3] }}
    transition={{ duration: 8, repeat: Infinity, ease: "easeInOut" }}
  />
  <motion.div
    className="absolute bottom-1/4 right-1/4 w-96 h-96 rounded-full bg-primary/10 blur-3xl"
    animate={{ scale: [1.2, 1, 1.2], opacity: [0.5, 0.3, 0.5] }}
    transition={{ duration: 10, repeat: Infinity, ease: "easeInOut" }}
  />

  <div className="relative z-10 max-w-5xl mx-auto text-center">
    {/* Badge - MUST INCLUDE */}
    <motion.div
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      transition={{ duration: 0.6 }}
      className="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-full border border-border bg-secondary/50 backdrop-blur-sm mb-8"
    >
      <Sparkles className="w-4 h-4 text-primary" />
      <span className="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Introducing the future of [your product]</span>
    </motion.div>

    {/* Main headline - USE font-display and text-gradient */}
    <motion.h1 
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 30 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      transition={{ duration: 0.7, delay: 0.1 }}
      className="font-display text-5xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6"
    >
      Build something{" "}
      <span className="text-gradient">extraordinary</span>
    </motion.h1>
    
    {/* Subheadline - USE text-muted-foreground */}
    <motion.p 
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 30 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      transition={{ duration: 0.7, delay: 0.2 }}
      className="text-lg md:text-xl text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12 leading-relaxed"
    >
      Transform your ideas into reality with our powerful platform. 
      Designed for creators who refuse to settle for ordinary.
    </motion.p>
    
    {/* CTA Buttons - USE hero variants and size="xl" */}
    <motion.div 
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 30 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      transition={{ duration: 0.7, delay: 0.3 }}
      className="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4"
    >
      <Button variant="hero" size="xl">
        Get Started Free
        <ArrowRight className="w-5 h-5" />
      </Button>
      <Button variant="heroOutline" size="xl">
        See How It Works
      </Button>
    </motion.div>

    {/* Stats - MUST INCLUDE for credibility */}
    <motion.div
      initial={{ opacity: 0 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1 }}
      transition={{ duration: 0.8, delay: 0.5 }}
      className="mt-20 grid grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-xl mx-auto"
    >
      {[
        { value: "10K+", label: "Active Users" },
        { value: "99.9%", label: "Uptime" },
        { value: "24/7", label: "Support" },
      ].map((stat, index) => (
        <motion.div
          key={stat.label}
          initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
          animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
          transition={{ duration: 0.5, delay: 0.6 + index * 0.1 }}
          className="text-center"
        >
          <div className="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-display font-bold text-primary">{stat.value}</div>
          <div className="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-1">{stat.label}</div>
        </motion.div>
      ))}
    </motion.div>
  </div>
</section>
```

FEATURE CARDS TEMPLATE (PROFESSIONAL VERSION):
```tsx
// IMPORTANT: Use lowercase import paths!
import { motion } from "framer-motion"
// Use REAL lucide-react icons - 6 DIFFERENT ICONS for 6 features
import { Zap, Shield, Palette, Rocket, Users, BarChart3 } from "lucide-react"

const features = [
  {
    icon: Zap,
    title: "Lightning Fast",
    description: "Optimized for speed with instant loading times and seamless interactions.",
  },
  {
    icon: Shield,
    title: "Secure by Default",
    description: "Enterprise-grade security protecting your data around the clock.",
  },
  {
    icon: Palette,
    title: "Beautiful Design",
    description: "Stunning interfaces crafted with attention to every pixel and detail.",
  },
  {
    icon: Rocket,
    title: "Scale Effortlessly",
    description: "Grow from prototype to production without missing a beat.",
  },
  {
    icon: Users,
    title: "Team Collaboration",
    description: "Work together in real-time with powerful collaboration tools.",
  },
  {
    icon: BarChart3,
    title: "Deep Analytics",
    description: "Understand your users with comprehensive insights and metrics.",
  },
];

<section className="relative py-24 px-4">
  <div className="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    {/* Section header - USE font-display */}
    <motion.div
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 20 }}
      whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      viewport={{ once: true }}
      transition={{ duration: 0.6 }}
      className="text-center mb-16"
    >
      <h2 className="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">
        Everything you need to{" "}
        <span className="text-gradient">succeed</span>
      </h2>
      <p className="text-muted-foreground text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Powerful features designed to help you build, launch, and grow your next big idea.
      </p>
    </motion.div>

    {/* Features grid - 6 cards with group hover effects */}
    <div className="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      {features.map((feature, index) => (
        <motion.div
          key={feature.title}
          initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 30 }}
          whileInView={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
          viewport={{ once: true }}
          transition={{ duration: 0.5, delay: index * 0.1 }}
          whileHover={{ y: -5, transition: { duration: 0.2 } }}
          className="group relative p-8 rounded-2xl bg-card border border-border hover:border-primary/50 transition-all duration-300"
        >
          {/* Hover glow effect - MUST INCLUDE */}
          <div className="absolute inset-0 rounded-2xl bg-primary/5 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-300" />
          
          <div className="relative">
            <div className="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-5 group-hover:bg-primary/20 transition-colors duration-300">
              <feature.icon className="w-6 h-6 text-primary" />
        </div>
            <h3 className="font-display text-xl font-semibold mb-3">{feature.title}</h3>
            <p className="text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">{feature.description}</p>
          </div>
    </motion.div>
  ))}
</div>
  </div>
</section>
```

‚ö†Ô∏è CRITICAL - LUCIDE-REACT ICONS:
You MUST use REAL icon names from lucide-react. Common valid icons include:
- Zap, Rocket, Star, Heart, Sparkles, Globe, Shield, Lock
- Users, Mail, Phone, Calendar, Clock, Check, X, Plus
- ArrowRight, ChevronDown, Menu, Search, Settings
DO NOT invent icon names like "FeatureIcon1" or "Icon1" - these don't exist!

TYPOGRAPHY GUIDELINES (STRICT):
- ALL headings MUST use font-display class
- Hero headline: font-display text-5xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-bold tracking-tight
- Section headlines: font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold
- Card titles: font-display text-xl font-semibold
- Body text: text-base or text-lg text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed
- CTAs: font-semibold
- Badge text: text-sm text-muted-foreground

SPACING & LAYOUT (GENEROUS):
- Sections: py-24 or py-32 (NOT py-20)
- Container: max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 (NOT max-w-7xl, we want more space)
- Card padding: p-8 (NOT p-6, bigger is better)
- Grid gaps: gap-6 or gap-8
- Button spacing: gap-4 between buttons
- Stats spacing: gap-8
- Section header margin-bottom: mb-16 (more breathing room)

ANIMATIONS (HIGH QUALITY):
- Initial animations: duration: 0.6-0.8, stagger delays: 0.1-0.2
- Infinite background animations: duration: 6-10s, ease: "easeInOut"
- Fade in on scroll: whileInView with viewport={{ once: true }}
- Card hover: whileHover={{ y: -5, transition: { duration: 0.2 } }}
- Button hover: Built into hero variant (scale: 1.05 + glow)
- Blur orbs: Different scales and opacities, opposite directions
- Stats: Staggered animation starting at delay: 0.6

RESPONSIVE DESIGN:
- Mobile-first approach
- Use Tailwind breakpoints: md:, lg:, xl:
- Stack on mobile, grid on desktop
- Adjust font sizes with responsive classes

CALL-TO-ACTION BUTTONS (USE NEW VARIANTS):
Hero section CTAs - MUST use these exact variants:
```tsx
<Button variant="hero" size="xl">
  Get Started Free
  <ArrowRight className="w-5 h-5" />
</Button>
<Button variant="heroOutline" size="xl">
  See How It Works
</Button>
```

Other sections - Use standard variants:
```tsx
<Button variant="default" size="lg">Action</Button>
<Button variant="outline" size="lg">Secondary</Button>
```

DO NOT use className overrides like "bg-gradient-to-r from-lovable-orange".
USE the built-in variants instead - they have better hover effects!

NAVIGATION:
```tsx
<nav className="fixed top-0 w-full bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-md border-b border-gray-200 z-50">
  <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 h-16 flex items-center justify-between">
    <div className="text-xl font-bold">Logo</div>
    <div className="hidden md:flex gap-6">
      {/* Nav links */}
    </div>
    <Button>Get Started</Button>
  </div>
</nav>
```

Remember: Create a landing page that converts visitors into users.
Focus on clear value propositions, social proof, and compelling CTAs.
Use the Lovable design system consistently throughout.
